{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Do not impose same-sex marriage on religious minorities",
        "additional_details": "The right of religious minorities not to have same-sex marriage imposed on them was guaranteed by the so-called \u2018quadruple lock\u2019 which was included in the Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013 when same-sex marriage was legalized in the UK.\r\n\r\nWe call on Parliament to continue to uphold and respect this fundamental human right.\r\n\r\nWe remind Parliament that one of its key functions in a democratic society is to protect minorities from the \u2018tyranny of the majority.\u2019",
        "background": "We call on Parliament, now and in the future, to continue to uphold the fundamental human right of religious minorities (Christians, Muslims, Jews and others) not to have same-sex marriage imposed on us, as guaranteed by the so-called \u2018quadruple lock\u2019 in the Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013.",
